Basic Tooltips

- Basic tooltips can be added using a simple @Override method into "appendToolTip()"
  For example:

`@Override
    public void appendTooltip(ItemStack stack, @Nullable World world, List<Text> tooltip, TooltipContext context) {
        tooltip.add(Text.literal("Tooltip Text #1").formatted(Formatting.GRAY));
        tooltip.add(Text.literal("Tooltip Subtext ").formatted(Formatting.DARK_GRAY));
    }`

- Note that a line indent can be added using "\n" then continuing the text.
  For example:

`@Override
    public void appendTooltip(ItemStack stack, @Nullable World world, List<Text> tooltip, TooltipContext context) {
        tooltip.add(Text.literal("Basic sword meant to \n prioritize mobility").formatted(Formatting.GRAY));
        tooltip.add(Text.literal("Right click to launch yourself forward quickly.").formatted(Formatting.DARK_GRAY));
    }`
